content.detailedDescription: My rock band random art festival on tour in colorado in '94 played an outdoor show at an abandoned copper mine in breckenridge co. we had a professional lighting setup with us and because the gig was outside at night and so high up in the mountains i predicted for two weeks before the gig that ufo's would show up. that night at around 3am - 4am multiple ufo's in formation were seen flying just overhead of the gig location. at least a hundred audience members and my 6 band members all witnessed this event. after finishing a song after playing for a few hours all who were in attendance started to point at the sky as a very very large double pyramidal ufo followed closely by a large spherical ufo both with much much smaller spherical ufo's which encircled both. 6-10 of the small sphere ufo's appeared to land upon the hillsides above the location where we were and across the valley. tall alien figures like apparitions seemed to appear near to where we were.
content.summary: Very large double pyramid ufo and many sphere ufos over breckenridge co in fall 1994

content.summary: Was on my deck and a red orb was to my left. as i looked another red orb raced to join  the first one

content.detailedDescription: At around 9:30 pm my neighbors the street were doing small ground fireworks in their driveway(nothing big that would pop in the sky). while sitting on my couch i caught sight of a red orb that appeared in sky above the tree line. my first thought was it was a firework, but it didn't explode or drift downward it instead glided nw.  i ran out of the house to get a better look and it was an orb gliding slowly in a nw direction pulsating red/orange. i ran back in to grab phone/camera and dragged my husband out. when i got back it was a much smaller orb still only red orange it hadn't traveled a long distance and it then just faded out.  i was unable to get photo.  approx 30 min later a plane traveled the same path but remained visible, with the flickering lights expected from a plane. ft. bragg and pope airforce base are both nearby i am used to seeing their aircraft during training.  this was different, it did not move as quickly it did not have flickering lights it remained a red orange orb. it did not drop it glided slowly and then fadeded quickly.
content.summary: During fireworks a reboot orb appeared, hovered, glided me then quickly dimmed out to nothing.

content.detailedDescription:
I was on my back deck throwing bread down for the birds to eat and i turned to the s.E. and the object caught my eye, i immediately reached in the door without taking my eyes off of it and grabbed my binoculars and wow...At first i thought it was a stealth then it moved to where i could see it was triangle shape. the whole underneath lit up then went off and did this a few times. the object would completely disappear and reappear a short distance from where i was looking. i also knocked on our kitchen window without taking my eyes off of the object to get my wife's attention but she was on the phone, now i'm the only one who saw this object and its really bothering me. i'm afraid to mention it to my neighbors... they'll probably think i'm strange and leaning on the fence. i've always been a skeptic with this subject but now i'm a firm believer. i kept watch on the object until it just vanished and so far it hasn't returned as far as i know but now i can't help watching the sky. i forgot to mention that the total time for observing it was a good 5 minutes or so and in that time a lot of thoughts go thru your head and still does.

i know it was a heavy triangle shaped machine and hovering, what upsets me is; am i the only person that witnessed it. and what was it doing here?
content.summary: Like watching a star wars movie, slowly appeared, the underneath lit up then lights went off then on again, disappeared and reappeared about 5 times.

content.detailedDescription:
Sitting on 3rd floor balcony watching fireworks on 4th of july at approx 2130 - 2200 facing wnw. noticed reddish dot of light ascending tree line approx 10 miles away followed closely by second one. initially thought it was fireworks but first light stopped ascending and second one caught up with it. then single point of light continued rising straight up for 10 seconds and turned to the north and flew basically in a straight line across the sky until it slowly faded from view. one or two more lights followed the same path that night and with all the fireworks going off i didn't think much of it.
the next night july 5th at pretty much the same exact time from the same exact location i saw another one ascending. this time i grabbed a pair of 16x binoculars and tried to view the object. also had my wife view it as well this time.
the were no red green navigation lights on it and while it looked reddish at the horizon it was bright orange in the sky. very difficult to resolve in binoculars due to fluctuating brightness levels and me shaking. i thought maybe chinese lanterns? but the speed it was traveling and the brightness didn't seem right. it would have had to be the size of a commercial airliner at that distance (which i have viewed multiple times with these binoculars) 
after following the sane wnw to n flight it faded from view.
then about 2 seconds later another one appeared on the horizon and followed the same exact flight plan!
had the wife watch this one through the binoculars, reported same observation as me but thought ie was more reddish at altitude.
followed it again until it disappeared and then a third and final one showed up and did the exact same route.
the only things that seem plausible are flares or chinese lanterns.
i don't believe a flare would ascend in that manner and last as song as these lights did. i've seen plenty of them in the military. but i'm no expert.
as for a chinese lanterns, they would have had to be enormous to put that much light out over that distance.
so sorry for writing a book but wanted to capture everything i could think of.
i thought about trying to film them on my iphone but it would have been another useless jumping dot of light claiming to be a ufo so i passed.
it was pretty awesome whatever it was!
content.summary: Observed 3 orange orbs ascend above tree line to wnw then turn north. one at a time lasted approx 3min.Appeared bright orange. viewed in 16x binoculars. no red green nav lights. no sound. viewed on 7/4/2115 and 7/5/2015 approx 10pm

content.detailedDescription: At home on west side of campbell ca. me and sisters friend planned to light off illegal firework soon after others in area started theirs,)we had only 1). we went to the school literately next block over to go light it off at 9.40 p.M.  we rode our bikes as not to get noticed, ( remind u we both r over 40 yrs of age). it was dark and their were a group of local kids  with an adult at other end of field.  as i was looking out to make sure their were no authorities around, i noticed an "object".  low and close! u could not notice it! fire works going off in neighborhood and this object slowly moved straight up!  straight right, straight left, straight down, straight up, for ten minutes! over neighborhood! this is also what was undeniably noticeable!, flashing ,two color lights only! sharp red( 5 seconds), sharp green (5 seconds), sharp red (5 seconds), sharp green( 5 seconds), continuously for 10 minutes! i pointed out to my sisters friend and he saw!  i think he couldn't accept what he was seeing because he just wanted to light the fuse and leave, but i kept pushing 4 him to acknowledge what i was seeing! he lit the fuse and we rode off.  he went back home and i went to go get closer,( as it was no more than a mile away).  i rode square mile and hears 2 men talking about it. i stopped and asked "what did they see". kind of same reaction like my sisters friend. not sure!  they called it a drone. as i rode square mile i had sight of it but stopped seeing it. it took me total 15 min till i got back home.  and their was my sisters friend in the front when i got back talking to the neighbors in the front. and the object was back!  viewing from the house now it continued to do same!  up.Down,left,right.  only in straight lines! they pretended not to notice. i have a feeling their r a lot of others who feel same! doesn't make sense that someone very local with supper expensive drone would only bring it out this 1 time on the 4th of july 2015, in a very close nit community ? i saw it slowly move away towards saratoga, cupertono area. i really would like it to be proven it was something not e.T.!  kind of freaky!
content.flightPath: Stationary,Hovering then path,Straight-line path,Path with directional change,Path then hovering
content.summary: If it wasn't most expensive drone hoover craft, then it was legit ufo !

content.detailedDescription:
My husband and i were getting ready to light off fireworks. i was looking up and noticed the first object floating in the sky. i noticed it because we had seen the same thing last year. it started off as one object floating in the sky, then about 5 minutes later a second object appeared. about every 5 to 10 minutes, another object appeared and followed the path of the others. each object drifted in an almost straight line, then made a sharp curve then flickered out. each object followed the exact same path as the last ones. i thought they were sky lanterns at first, but as we watched them, they seemed to communicate with each other by using light. one would flash brighter and dimmer and another one would respond by doing the same. they also reacted to the fireworks by flashing and mimicking the colors. we had seen the exact same thing last 4th of july, except the objects were coming from the direction they were going this year. i started to get afraid. my husband filmed them. we both got very nervous after that. we also saw a helicopter rushing across the sky seeming to chase the objects.

see video my husband posted to youtube this morning here:

[link moved to fi section/cms/tg]

content.detailedDescription:
Standing on south-side curb of elvira ave (street runs west-east) facing north during fireworks. observed green light similar in appearance to a planet or star on a clear night but somehow obviously not as distant -  initially appeared to be 5 miles away but seeing a wider radius of reported observers on this site. the stationary appearance of green object changing to red was noticeable. unsure of degrees from horizon - i am 6ft tall and light was spotted between and beyond powerlines running parallel to, and behind elvira houses across street. 

movements: after hovering stationary for quite some time, drifted swiftly eastward and remained stationary again (wind was blowing from ocean). it may have been led decorated drone with camera recording aerial fireworks. only question is when it descended and ascended in return to same spot - where did it go/land? it seemed to slowly drift back to previous location, then "dropped", then later re-ascended in original spot.

3 videos, 440 mb, exif data likely available. annoyingly and frustratingly, crappy camera quality in combination with night, smoke, haze, and street light make it a grainy picture, however, some video footage shows small plane/helicopter (also unidentifiable) cruising east to west on it's own journey while "start" hovers. (if media upload fails, then request dropbox).
content.summary: Distant star/aircraft

content.detailedDescription: On the night of july 5th around 10:10 pm i stepped outside on my porch to have a smoke. i happened to look to my south, when i noticed a low red/blue colored light. i didn't think anything of it at first but for some reason i couldn't stop watching it. after about 3 minutes of observing this light it moved a great distance to the northwest in about 5 seconds then stopped and hovered. i then noticed another very dim  pulsating white light a little farther north from the bigger orb. at first i thought the smaller white light was an aircraft but as it approached the bigger orb it looked like it was absorbed by it. after only finishing half of my cigarette i want in to get my phone so i could try and get it on camera but by the time i got back the light was gone. i might have been inside 2 minutes. the entire time i was watching this orb my hairs on my arms was standing up and i kept having this strange feeling of being watched. also i thought that i heard a hum from it. i do live half a mile from a major highway but i have never heard a sound like this from the highway
content.summary: First saw the object to the south, redish blue light, in about 5 seconds it moved a large distance to the northwest then stopped.

content.detailedDescription:
My family and i went out tonight to see the fireworks here in syracuse, ny... i think it was around around 9:15-9:30 pm est

we weren't there 3 minutes when my wife pointed something out to me and then i saw them over and over and over again.

orange orb like lights... reddish orange.

as everyone else was fixated on the massive fireworks display that seemed to engulf the entire city, i was looking out for these mysterious orange lights. i kept seeing them and pointing them out to my daughter.

they were moving southeast but they seemed to be moving up as well, as they would disappear from sight.  

but they kept coming...

it was getting a little creepy.

one of the orange orbs we were watching sped across the sky at a much faster rate than the others!

as the fireworks died down, we were trying to determine if we would go home or try to seek out more of these strange lights.  well we didn't have to think too long about that as we kept seeing them all around and so we drove throughout the city trying to get close to them.   

we saw two that looked like they would pass right over us and so we pulled over and that's where i got this one picture with my daughters phone as my battery was about to run out.


we kept driving around the city and kept seeing them... one off in the distance here... one there... two over here...

... and then we all saw a beautiful cluster of four!

i jumped out of the car to try and get a picture of the grouping but the phone wouldn't focus on them and i didn't get that picture.  :(

i have no idea what these were or if i'll see them again.

for a moment, as i was trying to come to some rational explanation, i thought of space debris burning up in the atmosphere as it crossed.  these never 'fizzled' out though and they seemed to have a distinct pulsation to them.

in all... on this 4th of july, i believe we counted at least 30 of these things.

it was weird but very cool!
content.flightPath: Stationary,Hovering then path,Straight-line path,Path with directional change,Path then hovering
content.summary: Syracuse, ny... july 4th 2015 during fireworks. over a two hour period, counted about 20-30 orbs.

content.detailedDescription: On july 4, 2014, myself and my 2 daughters reported seeing orb shaped objects (3) in night sky around 9 pm.  tonight, july 5th, 2015, in hopes of capturing object on film, myself and my daughter went outside and waited,hoping for another appearance of object, this time with binoculars and camera with telephoto lens.  around 9:15 pm, we observed one single reddish orange, orb shaped object travelling from east to north in a straight line trajectory.  i began taking photos and tracked the object until it disappeared going north.  once again, it had a smooth, mechanical, straight line trajectory.  if this is a satellite, it's almost as low in orbit as the iss, only the iss is not reddish orange in color.  it is also as bright as a star.
content.summary: Second night of seeing orb shaped, reddish orange object
